WEBVTT

00:04.038 --> 00:08.040
<i> - ♪ Ooh ♪</i>

00:08.142 --> 00:11.276
<i> ['50s doo-wop music]</i>

00:11.379 --> 00:18.117
<i> ♪ You made me love you ♪</i>

00:18.219 --> 00:20.853
<i> ♪ I didn't want to do it ♪</i>

00:20.955 --> 00:25.224
<i> ♪ I didn't want to do it ♪</i>

00:25.326 --> 00:31.897
<i> ♪ You made me want you ♪</i>

00:31.999 --> 00:35.234
<i> ♪ And all the time,</i>
<i> you knew it ♪</i>

00:35.336 --> 00:37.770
<i> ♪ I guess you always knew it ♪</i>

00:37.872 --> 00:39.638
- There you are.

00:39.740 --> 00:42.574
<i> - ♪ You made me happy... ♪</i>
- Oh, wow.

00:42.676 --> 00:45.010
<i> - ♪ Sometimes ♪</i>

00:45.112 --> 00:50.049
- You are beautiful.
Let's see you up close.

00:50.151 --> 00:53.452
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

00:53.554 --> 00:59.258
<i> - ♪ But there were times,</i>
<i> dear ♪</i>

00:59.360 --> 01:03.328
<i> ♪ You made me feel so bad ♪</i>

01:03.431 --> 01:06.398
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

01:06.500 --> 01:12.905
<i> ♪ You made me sigh for ♪</i>

01:13.007 --> 01:16.141
<i> ♪ I didn't want to tell you ♪</i>

01:16.243 --> 01:19.945
<i> ♪ I didn't want to tell you ♪</i>

01:20.047 --> 01:21.814
<i> ♪ I want some love ♪</i>

01:21.916 --> 01:23.248
- Hey, Daniel,
where you been?

01:23.350 --> 01:25.684
You can't take out
the boat like that.

01:25.786 --> 01:28.620
<i> - ♪ That's true,</i>
<i> yes, I do ♪</i>

01:28.722 --> 01:29.688
- Yo, Daniel.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.390
<i> [music stops abruptly]</i>

01:31.492 --> 01:33.025
- Hey.

01:33.127 --> 01:35.928
Sorry, I--I, uh,
just got here super early.

01:36.030 --> 01:37.429
I didn't--I didn't think
anyone would mind.

01:37.531 --> 01:38.897
- That's all right, man.

01:38.999 --> 01:41.166
Just don't let Susan catch you,
all right?

01:41.268 --> 01:43.268
You mind taking
the kids party today?

01:43.370 --> 01:46.505
- Sure, why not?
- Thanks.

01:47.575 --> 01:50.909
<i> [ominous music]</i>

01:51.011 --> 01:53.812
<i> [upbeat guitar music]</i>

01:53.914 --> 02:00.786
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

02:02.356 --> 02:04.623
- Come on, Kev. We're late.
- I don't feel good.

02:04.725 --> 02:06.458
- Uh-uh, no way.

02:06.560 --> 02:09.394
I invented fake sick when you
were a zygote. Get out.

02:09.497 --> 02:10.996
- No.

02:11.098 --> 02:13.098
- Kevin, I rearranged
my entire day

02:13.200 --> 02:14.433
to take you
to this stupid party,

02:14.535 --> 02:16.635
so that's what we're doing.
Get out.

02:18.706 --> 02:21.373
[scoffs]

02:21.475 --> 02:24.209
Okay, you wanna be
a child about this?

02:32.019 --> 02:33.051
[car beeps]

02:33.154 --> 02:35.120
Oh, Kev, I got you.

02:37.191 --> 02:39.858
Kevin, stop. Kev.

02:41.562 --> 02:42.594
Damn it.

02:42.696 --> 02:46.365
Kevin, what's wrong?

02:46.467 --> 02:48.300
Don't you wanna go tubing
with your friends?

02:48.402 --> 02:51.236
- They're not my friends.
You don't get it.

02:51.338 --> 02:52.671
- Well, I get it,

02:52.773 --> 02:54.473
and I'm gonna be
on the beach the entire time.

02:54.575 --> 02:56.909
If Jim tries pulling anything,
I'll put him in his place.

02:57.011 --> 02:59.478
- Just what I need.

02:59.580 --> 03:01.480
- You know what I mean.

03:01.582 --> 03:04.516
Listen, I won't let anything
bad happen to you, okay,

03:04.618 --> 03:08.053
as long as you can at least
pretend to enjoy yourself?

03:09.623 --> 03:11.390
- Fine.

03:13.427 --> 03:15.394
- That wasn't so hard,
was it?

03:15.496 --> 03:17.329
I feel like we should,
like, hug or something.

03:17.431 --> 03:19.765
- I don't think
we're there yet.

03:19.867 --> 03:21.366
- Hey.
- Hi.

03:21.468 --> 03:24.269
- [laughs]

03:24.371 --> 03:25.604
- Ugh!

03:25.706 --> 03:27.539
- Hey, Kev.
- Ugh.

03:27.641 --> 03:29.041
- Where's Carson?

03:29.143 --> 03:31.777
- I think he's meeting us here.
- Shut up.

03:31.879 --> 03:33.178
He didn't
text you back?

03:33.280 --> 03:35.714
- He's probably driving.
- Sure.

03:35.816 --> 03:37.249
- Rhi, I know you don't
like him, but can you just--

03:37.351 --> 03:38.917
- I have nothing
against Carson.

03:39.019 --> 03:41.353
I just don't necessarily
have anything for him.

03:41.455 --> 03:43.755
- Rhi, what are you wearing?
- Beach club.

03:43.857 --> 03:44.890
I'm dressed for the beach.

03:44.992 --> 03:46.024
- Go put something else
on quick

03:46.126 --> 03:47.459
before Ms. Conrad sees you.

03:47.561 --> 03:49.428
- Al, Susan Conrad
is nothing

03:49.530 --> 03:51.930
but a shallow,
stuck-up hag.

03:52.032 --> 03:53.999
- Correction: she's
a powerful, influential hag

03:54.101 --> 03:56.602
that can get me a letter
of recommendation for college.

03:56.704 --> 03:59.304
- Ali!
- Ah.

03:59.406 --> 04:01.006
Please behave.

04:01.108 --> 04:04.409
Hi, Mrs. Conrad.
Nice to see you.

04:04.511 --> 04:06.612
- Please, Alison,
call me Suze.

04:06.714 --> 04:08.413
After all, you and Carson

04:08.515 --> 04:10.482
have been dating
for what seems like forever.

04:10.584 --> 04:11.883
- Okay, Suze.

04:11.986 --> 04:14.219
- Are you Kevin's
chaperone today?

04:14.321 --> 04:15.520
- Uh, yeah,
for a bit.

04:15.623 --> 04:17.656
My mom's got a lot
on her plate.

04:17.758 --> 04:19.625
- Oh, I'm sure
she does, hon.

04:19.727 --> 04:21.260
It's great
to see you, Kevin.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.495
Jim was so excited when I
told him you were coming today.

04:23.597 --> 04:25.130
- I bet he was.

04:25.232 --> 04:27.199
- Yeah, they're
just over there.

04:28.669 --> 04:31.770
And I see that
you have brought a friend

04:31.872 --> 04:33.905
who had the super instinct

04:34.008 --> 04:35.841
to ignore
the club's dress code.

04:35.943 --> 04:38.143
- Aw, thanks.
You like it?

04:38.245 --> 04:39.911
- Oh, it's a look, hon.

04:40.014 --> 04:41.079
- Ooh, hey, there.
- Carson.

04:41.181 --> 04:42.848
- Hey, Mom. How's--oh.
- Hi.

04:42.950 --> 04:44.583
- What are you doing?
- I'm just having

04:44.685 --> 04:46.285
a lovely conversation
with Alison and her friend.

04:46.387 --> 04:49.454
- I'm sure you were.
- All right, enjoy yourselves.

04:49.556 --> 04:51.723
- We will, Mom.
- Bye.

04:51.825 --> 04:53.392
- Bye.

04:55.396 --> 04:57.095
- Are you sure
you're not adopted?

04:57.197 --> 04:59.998
- Oh, yeah, trust me,
I checked.

05:00.100 --> 05:02.100
Hi.
- Hi.

05:02.202 --> 05:03.635
- [scoffs]

05:03.737 --> 05:05.504
Someone call the police.
The fun killer's arrived.

05:05.606 --> 05:07.673
- Ah, stop trying to steal
my girlfriend, Rhi.

05:07.775 --> 05:09.441
- Green is a tragic color
on you, Carson.

05:09.543 --> 05:11.810
- What?

05:11.912 --> 05:13.211
- Why didn't you
answer her text?

05:13.314 --> 05:15.080
- I was driving.
- See?

05:15.182 --> 05:17.549
- You guys are gonna have to be
my eyes and ears out there.

05:17.651 --> 05:19.051
If you see one of your buddies
go down,

05:19.153 --> 05:21.253
you scream, "Man down!"
as loud as you can.

05:21.355 --> 05:23.221
That way, I'll come
and pick you guys up.

05:23.324 --> 05:25.357
Let me hear you try it.
all: Man down!

05:25.459 --> 05:27.125
- All right. Let's get
the life jackets on.

05:27.227 --> 05:28.660
We'll head out
on the water.

05:32.099 --> 05:33.765
- Sorry.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.400
- It's okay.

05:35.502 --> 05:37.469
- Just so you know,
the only reason my mom

05:37.571 --> 05:40.706
made me invite you
is 'cause your dad's dead.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.708
- Is everything okay
over here?

05:42.810 --> 05:46.712
- You bet.

05:46.814 --> 05:49.481
- I'm Daniel.
- Kevin.

05:49.583 --> 05:51.483
- Nice to meet you, Kevin.

05:51.585 --> 05:54.019
Don't listen to kids
like him, okay?

05:58.826 --> 06:01.660
<i> [hard rock music]</i>

06:01.762 --> 06:08.633
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:11.472 --> 06:13.672
all: Man down!

06:13.774 --> 06:18.243
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:18.345 --> 06:20.645
[cell phone rings]

06:24.017 --> 06:26.918
- Uh, yo, what's up?

06:30.924 --> 06:33.158
- I didn't say anything.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.394
- Whatever.

06:36.430 --> 06:38.363
- Here we go!

06:38.465 --> 06:40.766
[boat engine roaring]

06:40.868 --> 06:47.706
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

06:51.945 --> 06:54.713
all: Man down!

06:54.815 --> 07:01.620
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:07.461 --> 07:09.795
- You're cute.
- Okay.

07:09.897 --> 07:11.563
Yeah, I got to leave
the phone call.

07:11.665 --> 07:14.499
<i> [ominous music]</i>

07:14.601 --> 07:18.003
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:23.544 --> 07:25.076
- All right, how was that?
- That was great.

07:25.179 --> 07:27.979
- Good, good.
Who's next?

07:28.081 --> 07:29.448
- Kevin hasn't gone yet.

07:29.550 --> 07:31.683
- Ready to go, Kev?

07:34.087 --> 07:35.454
- Susan.
- Oh!

07:35.556 --> 07:37.022
- I am so sorry
I'm late.

07:37.124 --> 07:38.523
I had a last-minute
appointment.

07:38.625 --> 07:39.524
Hi, guys.

07:39.626 --> 07:42.093
- Diana.
It's okay, dear.

07:42.196 --> 07:44.496
I know you have to get
in extra hours when you can.

07:44.598 --> 07:45.597
Have a seat.

07:45.699 --> 07:47.132
- Thank you.
- Relax.

07:47.234 --> 07:48.900
- Thanks.
Where are the boys?

07:49.002 --> 07:50.635
- Oh, out on the water.

07:50.737 --> 07:52.604
It's so great to see
the boys together again.

07:52.706 --> 07:55.173
They used to be so close.

07:55.275 --> 07:57.509
Um, is everything
okay at home?

07:57.611 --> 07:59.144
- Thank you.

07:59.246 --> 08:00.111
Yeah, why?

08:00.214 --> 08:01.713
- Well, Jimmy told me

08:01.815 --> 08:03.748
Kevin had been dropped
from the honors program.

08:06.720 --> 08:09.688
- Kevin is just fine,
Susan.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.923
- Good. Good.

08:12.025 --> 08:14.826
<i> [ominous music]</i>

08:14.928 --> 08:21.833
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:32.813 --> 08:35.280
- Ready.
- All right, here we go.

08:35.382 --> 08:38.517
[boat motor revving]

08:38.619 --> 08:42.888
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:42.990 --> 08:44.556
- Let's cut him loose.

08:44.658 --> 08:46.491
- Whoo!

08:46.593 --> 08:47.959
[laughs]

08:48.061 --> 08:50.896
<i> [tense music]</i>

08:50.998 --> 08:56.868
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:56.970 --> 08:58.970
[laughter]

09:11.885 --> 09:14.219
[gasping]

09:14.321 --> 09:17.155
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

09:17.257 --> 09:24.095
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

09:31.371 --> 09:33.538
- Oh, uh...

09:39.813 --> 09:41.913
- Oh.

09:49.723 --> 09:51.856
Oh, my God.

09:51.959 --> 09:54.259
- Al?

09:54.361 --> 09:55.727
What's wrong?

09:58.565 --> 10:02.233
<i> [dramatic music swells]</i>

10:02.336 --> 10:05.003
- It's a shark! Kevin!

10:05.105 --> 10:07.105
Shark!

10:07.207 --> 10:08.273
[people screaming]

10:08.375 --> 10:10.809
- What's that all about?

10:10.911 --> 10:12.344
- Help!

10:12.446 --> 10:14.145
- Oh, my God, it's Kevin!
- What?

10:15.816 --> 10:17.649
- Kevin!

10:17.751 --> 10:20.919
- Shark!

10:21.021 --> 10:23.888
Kevin!
- Help!

10:25.659 --> 10:27.726
- Hang on, everybody.

10:27.828 --> 10:30.128
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:30.230 --> 10:32.097
- No, no, no.

10:32.199 --> 10:39.137
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

10:53.453 --> 10:55.153
[grunting]

10:56.423 --> 10:57.489
Ali!

11:08.168 --> 11:10.068
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

11:10.170 --> 11:11.836
[breathing heavily]

11:13.707 --> 11:14.572
[screams]

11:14.675 --> 11:17.008
- Kevin!
- Kevin!

11:20.514 --> 11:21.913
- [groans]

11:22.015 --> 11:24.482
- Kev, are you okay?

11:24.584 --> 11:26.418
- I'm okay.

11:27.821 --> 11:30.121
- Hey! Over here!

11:30.223 --> 11:33.058
Hey! Kev!
Kev, swim to the boat!

12:13.233 --> 12:15.266
- Kevin, don't worry, buddy.
Just keep swimming.

12:15.368 --> 12:17.302
I got you. I got you.
Come on.

12:20.707 --> 12:21.873
- Ali!

12:26.413 --> 12:27.579
- I'm coming, Kev!

12:27.681 --> 12:30.515
<i> [intense music]</i>

12:30.617 --> 12:37.422
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:38.725 --> 12:39.924
- I got you now.

12:40.026 --> 12:41.826
- [crying]

12:41.928 --> 12:44.896
- Okay, yeah,
I'll be fine.

13:02.716 --> 13:03.748
- Ali.

13:03.850 --> 13:05.683
- [whimpers]

13:05.786 --> 13:08.653
<i> [tender music]</i>

13:08.755 --> 13:09.954
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:10.056 --> 13:12.690
[siren wailing]

13:14.094 --> 13:15.627
- You all right,
young fella?

13:15.729 --> 13:17.228
- Mm-hmm.

13:17.330 --> 13:18.696
- All right,
this is gonna sting

13:18.799 --> 13:20.899
just a little bit,
all right?

13:23.637 --> 13:26.471
- Hey.

13:26.573 --> 13:27.906
Oh, my God,
I was so worried.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.574
- How dare you embarrass me
like that?

13:29.676 --> 13:30.875
- Mom, it was just a joke.

13:30.977 --> 13:32.477
- I'll be right back, okay?
- Okay.

13:34.214 --> 13:37.148
- Oh, wow, you're gonna have a
real gnarly scar there, buddy,

13:37.250 --> 13:38.449
a badge of honor.

13:38.552 --> 13:40.585
- I cannot
thank you enough.

13:40.687 --> 13:43.521
Really, thank you.

13:43.623 --> 13:45.323
- Thank you so much...

13:47.027 --> 13:48.860
Um...
- Daniel.

13:48.962 --> 13:51.963
- Ali.
- Alison?

13:52.065 --> 13:54.399
- Yeah. Have we met?

13:54.501 --> 13:57.101
No, um, you just--

13:57.204 --> 13:59.571
you remind me of someone
that I used to know.

14:01.608 --> 14:03.308
- Must be fate.

14:03.410 --> 14:05.577
Hey, I'm Rhiannon.

14:05.679 --> 14:06.711
- Must be.

14:06.813 --> 14:08.646
- Diana!

14:08.748 --> 14:10.281
Diana, Ali, Kevin.

14:10.383 --> 14:12.984
Hey, hey. Hey, what happened?
Hey, come here.

14:16.056 --> 14:17.322
Are you okay?

14:17.424 --> 14:20.992
- Yeah, yeah, I'm fine,
thanks to Daniel.

14:21.094 --> 14:22.794
- Who?

14:22.896 --> 14:25.296
- He was just here.

14:34.608 --> 14:38.643
- I knew you couldn't stay away
from me this time, baby.

14:38.745 --> 14:41.713
You're my everything,

14:41.815 --> 14:45.149
and I will do better this time,

14:45.252 --> 14:49.687
I promise.
I promise.

14:49.789 --> 14:52.624
<i> - We go now to 18-year-old</i>
<i> Alison Hooper...</i>

14:52.726 --> 14:53.791
- Ali, you're missing
your moment.

14:53.894 --> 14:55.193
<i> - And saw a shark.</i>

14:55.295 --> 14:57.028
<i> - It happened so fast.</i>

14:57.130 --> 14:58.796
<i> I saw Kevin with a shark--</i>

14:58.899 --> 15:00.832
Oh, God, could they
make me look worse?

15:02.168 --> 15:03.301
- Stop. You look fine.

15:03.403 --> 15:04.769
- No, your mother's
right, okay?

15:04.871 --> 15:06.404
The way your hair
is just matted to your face

15:06.506 --> 15:08.539
really
brings out your eyes.

15:08.642 --> 15:10.308
[laughs]

15:10.410 --> 15:12.410
<i> - The next thing I knew,</i>
<i> Daniel was there.</i>

15:12.512 --> 15:14.579
<i> - Daniel Kennedy,</i>
<i> the dockhand who rescued</i>

15:14.681 --> 15:16.481
<i> Alison and her brother</i>
<i> from the attack,</i>

15:16.583 --> 15:18.082
<i> just started working here</i>

15:18.184 --> 15:20.051
<i> at the Silver Sands Marina</i>
<i> last month.</i>

15:20.153 --> 15:22.487
- I thought I looked bad.
I can't even tell that's him.

15:22.589 --> 15:25.390
<i> [dramatic percussive music]</i>

15:25.492 --> 15:32.430
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

16:11.371 --> 16:13.905
<i> - So what does Susan say</i>
<i> about Daniel?</i>

16:14.007 --> 16:15.373
<i> - I never found</i>
<i> a good time to ask.</i>

16:15.475 --> 16:18.242
<i> She was too busy with Jim.</i>
<i> - [chuckles]</i>

16:18.345 --> 16:20.745
<i> Teaching him about kindness</i>
<i> and understanding, I'm sure.</i>

16:20.847 --> 16:25.583
<i> - The apple doesn't fall far</i>
<i> from the tree in that family.</i>

16:25.685 --> 16:27.685
<i> But you're right.</i>

16:27.787 --> 16:31.756
<i> We should really do something</i>
<i> for Daniel, thank him somehow.</i>

16:31.858 --> 16:34.892
<i> - Let's keep it simple,</i>
<i> have him over for dinner.</i>

16:34.995 --> 16:36.461
<i> - That is a great idea.</i>

16:36.563 --> 16:39.263
- I mean, somebody's gotta know
who this guy is.

16:39.366 --> 16:43.101
<i> - Well, I'll ask Susan about</i>
<i> him when she's calmed down.</i>

16:43.203 --> 16:45.837
<i> - Might take a while.</i>
<i> [chuckles]</i>

17:13.366 --> 17:16.200
<i> [tense music]</i>

17:16.302 --> 17:23.107
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:24.778 --> 17:26.744
- [screams]
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

17:26.846 --> 17:28.713
- Oh, my God.
- Everything okay up there?

17:28.815 --> 17:31.315
- Uh, yeah, I'm just
taking a shower, Mom.

17:31.418 --> 17:34.485
Carson, you're a creeper.
What are you doing?

17:35.622 --> 17:38.423
<i> [ominous music]</i>

17:38.525 --> 17:41.826
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:44.097 --> 17:46.397
- Oh, you didn't have to cook.
- Oh, well, I want to help out

17:46.499 --> 17:47.565
as much
as I can while I'm here.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.167
- That's nice.

17:49.269 --> 17:50.635
Having a full-time husband
that doesn't have

17:50.737 --> 17:52.737
to leave every other week
would be nicer.

17:52.839 --> 17:55.673
- It's my job, Di.
Can we not start?

17:55.775 --> 17:57.208
- I know.

17:59.179 --> 18:01.646
- Please don't do that in front
of young, impressionable eyes.

18:01.748 --> 18:03.614
- Morning, Ali.
Did you sleep okay?

18:03.716 --> 18:05.216
- Just great, Dad.

18:05.318 --> 18:07.585
Hey, look how nice that one is.
- Oh, that's great.

18:09.556 --> 18:11.889
Ali, I need you to take Kevin
to school again today.

18:11.991 --> 18:13.624
- What? Why?

18:13.726 --> 18:15.793
- Because you're going that
way and I have to work.

18:15.895 --> 18:18.729
- Wait a minute. Did he stop
taking the bus again?

18:18.832 --> 18:20.498
You gotta find out
what's going on with him, Di.

18:20.600 --> 18:21.933
- Ted, you know
he doesn't talk to me.

18:22.035 --> 18:24.001
The only reason I found out
about that party

18:24.104 --> 18:25.570
is because Susan called

18:25.672 --> 18:28.272
and asked
why he hadn't responded.

18:28.374 --> 18:29.507
- Hey, there, sporto.

18:29.609 --> 18:32.477
How's the leg feeling?
- Fine.

18:32.579 --> 18:34.545
- I made pancakes.

18:36.449 --> 18:37.648
- I'll be outside.

18:59.339 --> 19:04.742
- ♪ You make me want you ♪

19:04.844 --> 19:07.678
<i> [gentle music]</i>

19:07.780 --> 19:14.552
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:32.238 --> 19:35.239
[car engine sputtering]

19:37.777 --> 19:39.710
- Damn it.

19:48.788 --> 19:51.289
<i> [ominous music]</i>

19:51.391 --> 19:52.757
- Ali?
- Daniel?

19:52.859 --> 19:54.192
- I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to scare you.

19:54.294 --> 19:56.194
I was just--I was
heading to my car

19:56.296 --> 19:57.595
and I--I saw you there

19:57.697 --> 20:00.231
and...is there something
wrong with your car?

20:00.333 --> 20:03.134
- I don't know.
It's old and terrible.

20:03.236 --> 20:05.570
- Well, it looks like you
might need to get it towed.

20:05.672 --> 20:07.538
- Just what I need.

20:07.640 --> 20:09.006
Carson will be
out of practice soon.

20:09.108 --> 20:10.508
I can just wait for him.

20:10.610 --> 20:13.044
- Carson?
- Yeah, my boyfriend.

20:13.146 --> 20:14.712
- If you want,
I--I can give you a ride.

20:14.814 --> 20:16.847
- No, I couldn't
ask you to do that.

20:16.950 --> 20:18.216
You probably have
something better to do.

20:18.318 --> 20:20.885
- It's really no problem
at all.

20:21.921 --> 20:23.287
- You really don't have to.

20:23.389 --> 20:25.790
- Ali, please.
It will be my pleasure.

20:27.126 --> 20:29.760
- Okay, sure.

20:29.862 --> 20:31.529
<i> I'm sorry,</i>
<i> but I kinda feel</i>

20:31.631 --> 20:33.030
<i> like I got in a car</i>
<i> with a complete stranger.</i>

20:33.132 --> 20:34.832
- No, don't be sorry.

20:34.934 --> 20:37.101
I'm pretty much a stranger
giving you a ride, so I get it.

20:37.203 --> 20:38.736
- Don't get me wrong.
I'm really grateful

20:38.838 --> 20:41.639
for what you did, but yeah,
you are kind of a stranger.

20:41.741 --> 20:43.374
- Well, hopefully
we can remedy that.

20:43.476 --> 20:45.343
How is your brother Kevin?

20:45.445 --> 20:47.178
- He's good.
I usually pick him up

20:47.280 --> 20:49.080
after classes,
but I had to stay late today.

20:49.182 --> 20:50.815
- He seems like
a really good kid.

20:50.917 --> 20:52.149
- Yeah.

20:52.252 --> 20:54.385
He's had some rough patches
lately.

20:54.487 --> 20:56.520
My mom and Ted don't really
know what to do with him.

20:56.623 --> 20:59.123
- Is Ted your father?

20:59.225 --> 21:00.758
- Stepfather.

21:00.860 --> 21:02.994
Our dad died a few years ago.

21:04.697 --> 21:05.930
- I am so sorry.

21:06.032 --> 21:08.366
That--that was not
my place to pry.

21:08.468 --> 21:09.934
- It's okay.

21:18.244 --> 21:19.744
Thank you so much again,
Daniel.

21:19.846 --> 21:21.312
You're a lifesaver,
literally.

21:21.414 --> 21:23.748
- Please, don't even
mention it.

21:23.850 --> 21:26.584
Looks like your mom
is waiting for you.

21:26.686 --> 21:28.319
- Actually, she's
waiting for you.

21:28.421 --> 21:30.588
I texted her you
were coming, sorry.

21:30.690 --> 21:33.758
- No, that's--that's
no problem at all.

21:39.499 --> 21:41.299
- It's so good
to see you again, Daniel.

21:41.401 --> 21:43.067
- It's nice to formally
meet you, Mrs--

21:43.169 --> 21:44.535
- Please, call me Diana.

21:44.637 --> 21:46.304
No need for formalities
for our hero.

21:46.406 --> 21:48.439
- Oh.
- The car finally died,

21:48.541 --> 21:50.708
Mom, like, smoke-and-fire died.

21:50.810 --> 21:53.044
I'd still be stuck at school
if he wasn't walking by.

21:53.146 --> 21:55.579
- Well, it's a good thing
he was.

21:55.682 --> 21:58.149
Do you have any plans
for dinner, Daniel?

21:58.251 --> 21:59.483
- No, actually.

21:59.585 --> 22:01.385
- Why don't you come
over tonight?

22:01.487 --> 22:04.488
- I--I would love that,
if it's okay with you, Al.

22:04.590 --> 22:07.191
- Yeah, I know Carson
wants to thank you too.

22:08.161 --> 22:09.427
- Sounds great.

22:10.763 --> 22:13.130
Hello, Alison.
You look beautiful.

22:13.232 --> 22:15.666
Hi, Ali. Shh.

22:15.768 --> 22:17.935
Hi, Ali.
Hello, Alison.

22:18.037 --> 22:19.270
Hello, Alison.

22:19.372 --> 22:22.206
Hello, Alison.
You look beautiful.

22:22.308 --> 22:26.043
[whispering] Hello, Alison.
You look beautiful.

22:26.946 --> 22:29.647
[doorbell rings]

22:29.749 --> 22:32.883
Hello, Alison.
You look--hi, Kevin.

22:32.985 --> 22:35.319
- Hi, Daniel.
- Hello, Alison.

22:35.421 --> 22:36.654
You look beautiful.

22:36.756 --> 22:38.556
- Thanks. Come on in.

22:40.927 --> 22:43.294
- These are for you.
- Oh.

22:48.534 --> 22:50.768
- This must be Carson.

22:50.870 --> 22:52.870
- Thank you for saving
my Alison.

22:54.407 --> 22:57.141
- Daniel, you remember my mom,
and this is Ted.

22:57.243 --> 22:59.543
- These are for you, Diana.
- Oh, what are these for?

22:59.645 --> 23:03.147
- Well, a beautiful woman
always deserves flowers, Diana.

23:04.650 --> 23:07.551
- Thanks for coming, Dan.
- You bet.

23:09.956 --> 23:12.323
How's the leg, Kev?

23:12.425 --> 23:14.725
- It's a little sore.

23:14.827 --> 23:17.528
- I, uh--I heard there were
more sightings today.

23:17.630 --> 23:19.463
- Sharks are territorial,

23:19.565 --> 23:21.232
so they'll find a place
that they like

23:21.334 --> 23:23.734
and they will stake it out
until the food source runs out.

23:23.836 --> 23:25.803
- You sound like you know
a lot about them.

23:25.905 --> 23:27.905
- It's a bit of
an obsession of mine.

23:28.007 --> 23:31.942
I actually, uh--I had a run-in
with one myself

23:32.044 --> 23:34.845
that, uh, gave me
this bad boy right here.

23:34.947 --> 23:36.781
- Whoa, nice.
- Whoa.

23:36.883 --> 23:39.250
Did it hurt?
- Like you wouldn't believe.

23:39.352 --> 23:41.519
- How'd you get away?
- I don't really know.

23:41.621 --> 23:45.890
Um, as far as I could tell,
it was coming right at me,

23:45.992 --> 23:50.694
and then I just washed up
on the shore alive.

23:52.165 --> 23:53.998
- Wow, sounds like it
really ripped you apart.

23:54.100 --> 23:56.600
- Well, it could have,
but it didn't,

23:56.702 --> 24:01.172
and I like to think that, uh,
it just wasn't my time.

24:01.274 --> 24:03.541
There's still a lot of things
that I needed to get done,

24:03.643 --> 24:06.644
and...it's crazy.

24:06.746 --> 24:11.015
I've always had this connection
with sharks since then.

24:11.117 --> 24:12.316
I don't know.

24:12.418 --> 24:14.919
- Have you always worked
on the water?

24:15.021 --> 24:16.387
- I--I grew up
in a town like this,

24:16.489 --> 24:18.989
so I did what I had to do
to get by on my own.

24:19.091 --> 24:21.592
- No parents?

24:21.694 --> 24:24.161
- No, I, uh--
I--I lost my parents,

24:24.263 --> 24:28.265
but, uh, it's not really
something I like to talk about.

24:30.570 --> 24:32.703
- I'm sorry to hear that.

24:34.006 --> 24:35.439
- Is there a restroom
I can use?

24:35.541 --> 24:38.843
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:38.945 --> 24:41.412
- What are you doing
in here?

24:41.514 --> 24:44.048
- Oh, I saw the sink.

24:44.150 --> 24:46.984
I guess I got lost
looking for the bathroom.

24:47.086 --> 24:49.887
- It's right there.
- I guess it is.

24:49.989 --> 24:51.322
Um, sorry.
Is this your room?

24:51.424 --> 24:53.891
I didn't mean to invade
your personal space.

24:53.993 --> 24:56.227
- It's fine.
- Okay.

24:58.898 --> 25:02.500
- Well, we were beginning
to think you got lost up there.

25:02.602 --> 25:03.701
- I kinda did.

25:03.803 --> 25:05.436
There's a lot of rooms
up there.

25:05.538 --> 25:07.238
It's a beautiful home, though.
It's very comforting.

25:07.340 --> 25:09.173
- Thank you.
Sometimes it feels too big

25:09.275 --> 25:11.909
with Ted
being out of town all the time.

25:12.011 --> 25:14.378
- Well, actually,
we've been thinking about

25:14.480 --> 25:16.146
turning the old office

25:16.249 --> 25:18.449
into a guest room
and renting it out.

25:18.551 --> 25:20.217
- We have a guest room

25:20.319 --> 25:24.288
if the kids ever finish
clearing their stuff out of it.

25:24.390 --> 25:25.556
- Do you travel a lot?

25:25.658 --> 25:29.627
- A few days a month or so.

25:29.729 --> 25:31.061
- 11.

25:31.163 --> 25:32.696
- Who's counting?
- Well, it's nice to have

25:32.798 --> 25:34.965
a father figure around,
so you're lucky.

25:35.067 --> 25:38.369
I, uh--I wish my dad
and I got along.

25:38.471 --> 25:40.471
- I thought your parents
weren't around.

25:42.241 --> 25:43.874
- Uh, foster parents.

25:43.976 --> 25:46.143
- Oh.

25:47.880 --> 25:50.080
- Well, I, uh--I want
thank you guys

25:50.182 --> 25:51.882
for the hospitality.

25:51.984 --> 25:54.084
I should really be going,
but, uh,

25:54.186 --> 25:55.753
I haven't been
in town for long,

25:55.855 --> 25:58.822
so it's nice to finally meet
some good friends.

25:58.925 --> 26:00.758
- Please, it's honestly
the least we could do.

26:00.860 --> 26:02.860
- Dan, don't be a stranger.
I mean it.

26:02.962 --> 26:05.262
- I will not be.

26:06.198 --> 26:08.566
Ali, I'll see you around.

26:08.668 --> 26:09.667
- Okay.

26:09.769 --> 26:12.469
<i> [eerie music]</i>

26:12.572 --> 26:14.305
Bye.
[door clicks]

26:17.009 --> 26:18.242
<i> - I don't care what they say.</i>

26:18.344 --> 26:20.010
You find the shark
and get rid of it.

26:20.112 --> 26:21.779
The club's insurance
is already gonna be wrecked

26:21.881 --> 26:23.948
after what happened
to that kid.

26:31.457 --> 26:32.990
- Hey, Mom, I'll be right back.

26:33.092 --> 26:35.893
<i> [tense music]</i>

26:35.995 --> 26:42.833
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:00.953 --> 27:03.120
[car engine turns over]

27:27.413 --> 27:30.214
[window squeaks]

27:40.926 --> 27:42.459
[window slams]

27:44.964 --> 27:47.765
<i> [tense music]</i>

27:47.867 --> 27:54.705
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:17.596 --> 28:20.397
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

28:20.499 --> 28:27.404
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:05.344 --> 29:07.177
[loud clatter]

29:11.951 --> 29:14.718
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

29:14.820 --> 29:21.759
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:24.130 --> 29:26.396
- He's gonna come
between us, baby,

29:26.499 --> 29:30.467
but you know I won't let that
happen, my Alison.

29:30.569 --> 29:33.103
You're my everything.

29:33.205 --> 29:35.973
<i> [tense music]</i>

29:36.075 --> 29:43.013
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:44.650 --> 29:48.786
<i> [music swells dramatically]</i>

29:48.888 --> 29:52.256
[grunting]

29:55.694 --> 29:58.862
When I got back home from work,
the front door was open,

29:58.964 --> 30:00.664
and I should have known better.

30:00.766 --> 30:03.534
I really should have,
but I--I went in there.

30:05.137 --> 30:08.238
These three guys,
they just--

30:08.340 --> 30:09.873
they were
stealing everything, God.

30:09.975 --> 30:13.944
They just trashed the place.
Thank you.

30:14.046 --> 30:15.546
I tried to stop them, you know?

30:15.648 --> 30:18.782
I really tried to stop them.
I was just outnumbered.

30:18.884 --> 30:21.185
- That's terrible, Dan.
What did the cops say?

30:21.287 --> 30:23.320
- There was not much
they could do, you know?

30:23.422 --> 30:26.356
I tried to get a good look
at them, but they ran away.

30:27.860 --> 30:31.461
They, uh, told me
to just change the locks

30:31.564 --> 30:33.430
when I get back there.

30:33.532 --> 30:36.633
I just--I feel so invaded,
you know?

30:36.735 --> 30:38.235
It's scary.

30:38.337 --> 30:39.369
- Well, don't worry.
You're staying here

30:39.471 --> 30:40.838
with us tonight.
- No, no.

30:40.940 --> 30:42.139
- Yes.
- No, I couldn't.

30:42.241 --> 30:43.440
I really couldn't.

30:43.542 --> 30:44.741
- Of course you can.

30:44.844 --> 30:46.410
- You saved our kids
from that shark.

30:46.512 --> 30:48.812
It's the least we can do.

30:48.914 --> 30:51.982
- Just--I'm not used to
people being this nice to me.

30:54.920 --> 30:58.989
- Dan, the spare room is yours
as long as you need it.

30:59.091 --> 31:00.290
- Really?

31:00.392 --> 31:01.658
- I'd feel a lot better
leaving town

31:01.760 --> 31:03.861
knowing our family's hero
is here.

31:03.963 --> 31:06.597
- Thank you. Thank you.

31:07.533 --> 31:10.334
<i> [tender piano music]</i>

31:10.436 --> 31:17.374
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:20.312 --> 31:22.512
Sorry.
- Don't be sorry.

31:22.615 --> 31:24.448
- Jeez, they did a number
on you.

31:24.550 --> 31:25.649
I'm glad you're okay.

31:25.751 --> 31:27.017
Do you need help
making the bed?

31:27.119 --> 31:28.685
- No, I should be good.

31:28.787 --> 31:30.454
Is that your artwork?

31:30.556 --> 31:33.056
- Yeah, from junior high
though, so...

31:33.158 --> 31:34.625
- You're very talented.

31:34.727 --> 31:36.260
- Thanks.

31:36.362 --> 31:39.529
Well, uh, let me know
if you need anything.

31:39.632 --> 31:45.535
- Yeah, um, are you okay
with me being here, Ali?

31:45.638 --> 31:48.272
- Yeah, definitely.

31:50.009 --> 31:51.742
- Good.

31:52.745 --> 31:54.378
- Good night.
- Night.

31:57.650 --> 31:58.649
[sighs]

32:00.085 --> 32:03.020
[toilet flushing]

32:05.591 --> 32:07.457
Hey, buddy.

32:07.559 --> 32:08.759
- Hey.

32:08.861 --> 32:10.560
I heard about
the break-in.

32:10.663 --> 32:13.764
Dude, I--I'm sorry, man.
That sounds rough.

32:13.866 --> 32:15.198
- Yeah. It really sucks

32:15.301 --> 32:19.436
when somebody just
goes through your belongings,

32:19.538 --> 32:22.406
traipses around
where they don't belong.

32:22.508 --> 32:24.474
- I can imagine.

32:24.576 --> 32:26.209
- Don't worry.

32:26.312 --> 32:29.479
Your secret's safe with me.

32:29.581 --> 32:31.581
- What?
- I won't tell Diana

32:31.684 --> 32:33.250
that you're spending the night.

32:33.352 --> 32:36.153
- Oh, oh, yeah,
yeah, yeah, thanks, man.

32:36.255 --> 32:37.087
- [clicks tongue]
Yeah.

32:37.189 --> 32:38.422
- Yeah.
- Night.

32:38.524 --> 32:40.824
- Mm-hmm.

32:40.926 --> 32:43.760
<i> [ominous music]</i>

32:43.862 --> 32:49.366
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:49.468 --> 32:50.634
- So he's just gonna
stay there?

32:50.736 --> 32:53.403
- I guess.
It was all Diana.

32:53.505 --> 32:55.973
He needed a room.
We had a room.

32:56.075 --> 32:58.909
- Don't go pissing on my leg
and tell me it's raining.

32:59.011 --> 33:00.677
- What?

33:00.779 --> 33:02.846
Dan doesn't know anyone else
in town, and my mom loves him.

33:02.948 --> 33:05.248
- Well, what's not to love?
If you don't plan

33:05.351 --> 33:07.351
on test-driving that car,
hand over the keys.

33:07.453 --> 33:09.086
- Does that mean you want me
to put in a good word?

33:09.188 --> 33:10.787
- Sure.

33:10.889 --> 33:12.990
I mean, it can't be any worse
than my last few dates.

33:13.092 --> 33:16.460
Besides,
I always have my mace.

33:16.562 --> 33:17.995
- You do.
- Right?

33:19.765 --> 33:21.965
- Well, he's coming to pick me
up this afternoon.

33:22.067 --> 33:23.433
- A roommate
and a chauffeur?

33:23.535 --> 33:24.701
- He's just helping me out
with rides

33:24.803 --> 33:27.137
until I get my car
back from the shop.

33:27.239 --> 33:30.707
- So, wait, Carson is okay
with another piece of man candy

33:30.809 --> 33:32.376
living
across the hall from you?

33:32.478 --> 33:35.112
- Well, I haven't exactly
told Carson yet.

33:35.214 --> 33:38.448
- Told Carson what?

33:38.550 --> 33:40.817
<i> I don't know. I thought he was</i>
<i> just staying for the night.</i>

33:40.919 --> 33:42.586
<i> - I don't know what</i>
<i> the big deal is, Carson.</i>

33:42.688 --> 33:44.054
<i> - The big deal is that</i>
<i> you're my girlfriend</i>

33:44.156 --> 33:45.922
<i> and the guy</i>
<i> gives me the creeps.</i>

33:47.459 --> 33:49.359
I don't like the way
he looks at you, okay?

33:49.461 --> 33:51.495
- Sure, he's, like,
a little strange.

33:51.597 --> 33:53.263
Don't you trust me?
- I trust you.

33:53.365 --> 33:54.731
I don't trust him.

33:54.833 --> 33:58.668
- Same difference.
- Ali, Ali, I'm serious.

34:00.339 --> 34:02.339
I need you
to see something, okay?

34:02.441 --> 34:04.307
I--I'm not sure
he is who he says he is.

34:04.410 --> 34:06.076
- What, are you
spying on him?

34:06.178 --> 34:07.844
- Well, I told you.

34:07.946 --> 34:09.980
I--I got a bad vibe.
He's a creep.

34:10.082 --> 34:12.682
- The only one acting like
a creep is you, Carson.

34:12.785 --> 34:14.651
Now, what do you want
to show me?

34:16.388 --> 34:19.089
- You--you need
to trust me, okay?

34:19.191 --> 34:21.358
I--I don't want you
around him.

34:21.460 --> 34:22.959
- Do you know
how insane you sound

34:23.062 --> 34:24.895
after you promised me
you'd drop it?

34:24.997 --> 34:27.364
[cell phone rings]

34:30.335 --> 34:32.636
- Um, Ali,
where are you going?

34:32.738 --> 34:33.770
- My ride is waiting.

34:33.872 --> 34:36.740
<i> [dark music]</i>

34:36.842 --> 34:43.647
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:48.420 --> 34:50.887
- I'm totally gonna have to
steal this one from you.

34:50.989 --> 34:52.889
- Keep it.
That one's bad luck.

34:52.991 --> 34:56.793
- So did you guys
break up?

34:56.895 --> 34:58.728
- No, we're
just fighting.

34:58.831 --> 35:00.997
- Well, that's what you get
for dating high school boys,

35:01.100 --> 35:03.567
not real men.
They're so jealous.

35:03.669 --> 35:05.368
- I don't know.
Maybe he has a point.

35:05.471 --> 35:07.804
Dan is a little severe,
I guess.

35:07.906 --> 35:09.906
What if he does have
a thing for me?

35:10.008 --> 35:12.375
Maybe I should talk to my mom
about asking him to leave.

35:12.478 --> 35:14.444
- Or you could set him up
with me,

35:14.546 --> 35:18.849
get Carson off your back,
two birds, one stone.

35:20.586 --> 35:23.887
- Hey, Dan.
- Hey, Ali.

35:23.989 --> 35:25.655
- You remember
my friend Rhiannon.

35:25.757 --> 35:27.224
- Yeah, you were
at the beach, right?

35:27.326 --> 35:29.059
- Yeah, sure was.

35:29.161 --> 35:30.193
- Well, you look
beautiful.

35:30.295 --> 35:31.928
Are you going somewhere?

35:34.366 --> 35:37.501
- Beach party at Claire's.
Wanna come?

35:37.603 --> 35:39.603
- I'm going with Carson,
so Rhi needs a date.

35:41.440 --> 35:43.840
- And if we get bored,
I can show you around town.

35:43.942 --> 35:45.475
I know all the best places,

35:45.577 --> 35:48.011
right next
to all the worst places.

35:48.113 --> 35:49.813
It's a small town.

35:49.915 --> 35:51.948
- Sure.
- Great.

35:52.050 --> 35:54.084
- Why not?

35:56.054 --> 35:59.723
- Hey, Ali.
I--oh, oh, okay.

35:59.825 --> 36:04.060
Hey, hey, I'm s--I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, Ali.

36:04.163 --> 36:07.197
You're right.
I was jealous.

36:07.299 --> 36:10.901
- And an ass.
- And an ass.

36:12.171 --> 36:13.703
- You were wrong too.

36:13.805 --> 36:17.407
Looks like Dan's taking
a liking to Rhiannon, not me.

36:17.509 --> 36:20.110
- Whoa, looks like someone's
getting lucky tonight.

36:20.212 --> 36:21.778
- Stop, they just met.

36:21.880 --> 36:23.513
- Maybe I wasn't talking
about them.

36:23.615 --> 36:25.182
[pop music over stereo]

36:25.284 --> 36:28.785
- ♪ Your words, they just
cut straight through me ♪

36:28.887 --> 36:31.655
♪ Is this what you want? ♪

36:31.757 --> 36:34.758
- What did you want
to show me?

36:34.860 --> 36:35.859
- Forget it.

36:42.034 --> 36:43.833
- Hey, Dan.
Having a good time?

36:43.936 --> 36:46.102
- Amazing.
It's--it's good.

36:46.205 --> 36:47.904
- Hey, what's up?

36:48.006 --> 36:49.873
- I was just on my way back,
but I was wondering

36:49.975 --> 36:52.542
if you guys
wanted to come sit by the fire.

36:52.644 --> 36:54.711
- I've got a better idea.

36:54.813 --> 36:56.613
Wanna go for a walk?
- Really?

36:56.715 --> 36:59.716
I feel like--I feel like
we just got here.

36:59.818 --> 37:02.452
- Oh, I mean, we can stay,
if you want.

37:03.722 --> 37:08.058
- No, yeah,
let's--let's head out of here.

37:09.394 --> 37:12.095
You know,
I love that dress on you.

37:12.197 --> 37:14.030
- Thanks, it's Al's,

37:14.132 --> 37:16.399
but I think
it's better on me, don't you?

37:16.501 --> 37:19.369
- Are you and Ali close?
- Yeah.

37:19.471 --> 37:21.805
We've been best friends
since we were kids.

37:21.907 --> 37:23.907
She's my ride or die.

37:24.009 --> 37:27.110
- That's sweet, I think.

37:27.212 --> 37:30.247
How long has, uh,
she been with Carson?

37:30.349 --> 37:33.450
- I don't know,
a couple years now.

37:33.552 --> 37:35.785
- Is he a good guy?

37:35.887 --> 37:38.021
- He's got the personality
of a wet mop.

37:38.123 --> 37:41.258
- Mm.
- But she's really into him,

37:41.360 --> 37:43.526
which I guess is
all that really matters.

37:44.796 --> 37:47.030
- Are things serious
between them?

37:47.132 --> 37:51.434
- He's safe, if you're
into that sort of thing.

37:51.536 --> 37:53.370
Plus his mother's loaded.

37:53.472 --> 37:55.372
Ali's been trying
to impress her to no avail

37:55.474 --> 37:58.241
since the moment
they met.

38:10.255 --> 38:12.122
Is everything okay?

38:13.492 --> 38:15.058
- It's fine.

38:17.229 --> 38:19.095
- Do you not want to kiss me?

38:20.799 --> 38:22.299
Daniel?

38:25.504 --> 38:27.671
What--are you crazy?

38:28.907 --> 38:30.940
Maybe you are crazy.

38:31.043 --> 38:33.443
Now what am I gonna do
about this wet dress?

38:33.545 --> 38:35.445
- Oh, leave it.

38:35.547 --> 38:38.381
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

38:38.483 --> 38:44.821
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:47.492 --> 38:49.125
What's going on?

38:49.928 --> 38:51.428
- Oh, Dave Burke.

38:51.530 --> 38:54.164
I was hired to take care
of your fish problem.

38:54.266 --> 38:55.899
- The shark?
- Yes, sir.

38:56.001 --> 38:57.934
- You're not planning on
killing her, are you?

38:58.036 --> 39:01.137
- Nah, I'm just gonna catch it
and throw it back in.

39:01.239 --> 39:03.106
Of course
I'm going to kill it.

39:03.208 --> 39:04.874
- You know, she never even
really hurt anybody.

39:04.976 --> 39:06.476
The kid just had a scratch.

39:06.578 --> 39:08.211
- Listen, man, I don't have
anything personal

39:08.313 --> 39:09.579
against sharks.

39:09.681 --> 39:10.747
I was hired to do a job.

39:10.849 --> 39:12.682
Want to give me a hand?

39:14.086 --> 39:15.719
- Sure.

39:21.827 --> 39:23.126
- It was so fun.

39:23.228 --> 39:24.427
At first, I didn't think
he was into it,

39:24.529 --> 39:26.496
and then it was like
a switch went off, and wow.

39:26.598 --> 39:29.132
- Good.
Any plans to see him again?

39:29.234 --> 39:31.000
- Not yet,
but I'm working on it.

39:31.103 --> 39:32.669
- Okay.
- Oh, Alison,

39:32.771 --> 39:34.304
I'm glad I caught you.

39:34.406 --> 39:35.538
I need to talk to you
about your portfolio.

39:35.640 --> 39:36.539
- I'm sorry it was late,
Mr. Slade.

39:36.641 --> 39:37.841
It won't happen again.

39:37.943 --> 39:39.342
- You've been chosen
by the department

39:39.444 --> 39:40.744
for the gallery showing
at Silver Sands.

39:40.846 --> 39:42.078
- Really?
- It's Thursday night.

39:42.180 --> 39:43.413
You don't want to miss it.

39:43.515 --> 39:45.181
- Thank you so much.

39:45.283 --> 39:47.417
- Well, color me
lime green Jell-O.

39:47.519 --> 39:49.652
Congratulations.

39:55.627 --> 39:57.394
- Hey, Kev.
- Hi.

39:57.496 --> 39:59.129
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, hold on
a second. What's going on here?

39:59.231 --> 40:00.463
- I fell.

40:00.565 --> 40:01.998
- You fell?
Oh, come on, man.

40:02.100 --> 40:04.167
Let's talk about this.
You could trust me.

40:04.269 --> 40:07.170
- Get off me!
You're not my father.

40:09.241 --> 40:11.975
- Oh, Kev, what's wrong?

40:13.178 --> 40:14.844
[door slams]

40:18.550 --> 40:19.916
- I'm serious, Di.

40:20.018 --> 40:21.484
He needs to talk to someone.
- Oh, great.

40:21.586 --> 40:23.319
You think I'm doing
such a terrible job.

40:23.422 --> 40:25.054
- That has nothing
to do with it.

40:25.157 --> 40:27.323
He's having trouble at school.
He won't talk to us.

40:27.426 --> 40:28.992
He needs a professional to
help him deal with all of this.

40:29.094 --> 40:30.560
[knock on door]
- Go away.

40:30.662 --> 40:32.061
- I wanted him to see
someone after the accident.

40:32.164 --> 40:33.830
I can't just force him.

40:33.932 --> 40:36.166
- You're his mother.
That's exactly what you can do.

40:42.140 --> 40:43.239
- They hate me.

40:43.341 --> 40:46.009
- No, nobody hates you.

40:46.111 --> 40:48.945
- Mom and Dad used to fight
like that all the time.

40:49.047 --> 40:50.847
I wish Ted would just leave.

40:50.949 --> 40:53.316
- You want to tell me
who gave you that black eye?

40:53.418 --> 40:55.385
- No.

40:55.487 --> 40:57.687
- It was Jim,
wasn't it?

40:59.858 --> 41:02.859
You know, there's always
gonna be a Jim in your life,

41:02.961 --> 41:05.128
someone so insecure,
they just want to take it out

41:05.230 --> 41:07.597
on someone smaller
than themselves.

41:07.699 --> 41:11.100
You gotta learn
to stick up for yourself.

41:11.203 --> 41:14.170
- I guess.
- Here.

41:14.272 --> 41:18.408
Anybody gives you a hard time
again, you just use this.

41:18.510 --> 41:20.243
<i> [dramatic musical flourish]</i>

41:20.345 --> 41:23.980
Go ahead, take it, but don't
tell anyone about this.

41:24.082 --> 41:25.748
It's our little secret.

41:25.851 --> 41:28.685
<i> [tense music]</i>

41:28.787 --> 41:29.986
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:30.088 --> 41:31.454
Atta kid.

41:35.927 --> 41:37.927
- Hey, hey, how's he doing?

41:38.029 --> 41:40.029
- Oh, he's gonna
be just fine.

41:40.131 --> 41:43.132
- Thank you. Ted has no clue
how to talk to him.

41:43.235 --> 41:44.400
He's pretty much useless,
you know?

41:44.503 --> 41:46.035
- I've noticed.

41:46.137 --> 41:47.670
You think it would
be better for you guys

41:47.772 --> 41:51.574
if he just wasn't
in the picture?

41:51.676 --> 41:53.309
- I don't know, maybe.

41:53.411 --> 41:55.545
He's not like my dad,
that's for sure.

41:55.647 --> 41:56.679
- Hmm.

42:03.021 --> 42:04.220
<i> - Call me tonight.</i>

42:04.322 --> 42:05.922
- You know I will.
- Okay.

42:06.024 --> 42:08.191
- I love you.
- I love you too.

42:08.293 --> 42:11.160
<i> [ominous music]</i>

42:11.263 --> 42:15.498
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:15.600 --> 42:17.133
- Hey, Ted.
- Yeah?

42:17.235 --> 42:18.902
- Would you mind giving me
a ride to the marina?

42:19.004 --> 42:20.270
I think it's on the way,

42:20.372 --> 42:21.804
and my car,
it's been acting up.

42:21.907 --> 42:23.840
- Yeah, no problem.
- Thank you.

42:23.942 --> 42:25.408
I really appreciate it.

42:29.447 --> 42:31.114
- So how's the room
treating you?

42:31.216 --> 42:33.016
- Oh, it's--it's just great.

42:33.118 --> 42:36.152
It's exactly what I needed
until I get my place fixed.

42:36.254 --> 42:37.887
- We really like
having you around.

42:37.989 --> 42:39.556
Plus we're not
home very often,

42:39.658 --> 42:41.658
so it's--it's great
to have someone with the kids.

42:41.760 --> 42:44.527
- Oh, well,
I'd do anything for them.

42:44.629 --> 42:45.728
Are you gonna be gone long?

42:45.830 --> 42:48.331
- Eh, just a few days.
- Mm.

42:48.433 --> 42:51.334
You know, Ali and Kevin
don't really like you, Ted.

42:51.436 --> 42:54.270
In fact, they'd prefer it
if you just died.

42:54.372 --> 42:56.105
- What?
- Yeah.

42:56.207 --> 42:58.908
They told me last night.

42:59.010 --> 43:01.578
- Well, you know, they're
having a really rough time

43:01.680 --> 43:04.714
since Andrew passed.
- Yeah.

43:04.816 --> 43:06.683
Kevin really needs
a father figure,

43:06.785 --> 43:07.951
though,
don't you think,

43:08.053 --> 43:10.386
someone that he can
kinda look up to?

43:10.488 --> 43:12.989
- Excuse me?
- I'm sorry, Ted.

43:13.091 --> 43:15.058
You seem like
a really decent guy.

43:15.160 --> 43:17.193
- [screaming]

43:17.295 --> 43:20.296
[car engine revs]

43:20.398 --> 43:21.564
Watch out!

43:21.666 --> 43:23.199
You're gonna get us killed!

43:23.301 --> 43:24.767
- I will be just fine.

43:24.869 --> 43:27.103
[tires squealing]

43:31.276 --> 43:34.243
<i> [intense music]</i>

43:34.346 --> 43:35.545
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:35.647 --> 43:37.814
[truck horn honks]

43:37.916 --> 43:40.817
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:40.919 --> 43:44.120
<i> [intense music fades]</i>

43:44.222 --> 43:47.824
[whistling
"You Made Me Love You"]

43:47.926 --> 43:54.831
♪ ♪

43:57.335 --> 43:59.502
[device beeping]

44:02.040 --> 44:03.573
It's pretty neat, huh?

44:03.675 --> 44:05.508
I can't believe I didn't think
about this before,

44:05.610 --> 44:07.343
tagging the shark to track it.

44:08.346 --> 44:12.181
Hey, wake up.

44:12.283 --> 44:13.650
- [muffled scream]

44:13.752 --> 44:15.418
- It's a little late in the day
for feeding time,

44:15.520 --> 44:18.187
but sometimes you just have
to spoil them, you know?

44:18.289 --> 44:21.124
<i> [ominous music]</i>

44:21.226 --> 44:28.064
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

44:32.570 --> 44:35.972
Oh, thank you.
- [whimpers]

44:36.074 --> 44:37.507
- Let's get you up
and toasty.

44:37.609 --> 44:40.610
- [muffled grunting]

44:41.646 --> 44:43.346
- And don't you worry, Ted.

44:43.448 --> 44:45.114
I'm gonna take
great care of them.

44:45.216 --> 44:47.550
They're my family now.

44:47.652 --> 44:50.286
- [muffled speech]

44:56.728 --> 44:59.896
- Send a message to Diana:

44:59.998 --> 45:03.232
"Sorry, late night.

45:03.334 --> 45:06.502
Love you. Good night."

45:19.084 --> 45:21.951
- Uh, good morning.
- Good morning.

45:22.053 --> 45:24.087
- You know, I could
get used to seeing you

45:24.189 --> 45:27.323
every day when I wake up.
- That sounds nice.

45:29.360 --> 45:32.428
Now get moving
before Diana catches you.

45:33.865 --> 45:35.765
Wait, I didn't tell you.

45:35.867 --> 45:37.500
What are you doing Thursday?

45:37.602 --> 45:39.469
- Oh, we have
practice tomorrow. Why?

45:39.571 --> 45:42.205
- I was chosen for
the gallery show at the club.

45:42.307 --> 45:44.907
- Ali, that's great.
Well, I--

45:45.009 --> 45:47.410
- I was hoping you'd be able
to come with me.

45:47.512 --> 45:49.178
- What time does it start?

45:49.280 --> 45:52.148
- 8:00.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, good.

45:52.250 --> 45:54.417
No, I'll go to practice,
get ready,

45:54.519 --> 45:56.819
and then I'll head
to your place after.

45:56.921 --> 45:58.788
- Does that mean you're coming?
- Yes, of course.

45:58.890 --> 46:01.624
I'm so proud of you.

46:05.697 --> 46:07.063
- What?

46:13.138 --> 46:14.837
What are you doing?

46:14.939 --> 46:16.739
- I think he was
spying on us.

46:16.841 --> 46:19.208
- You're so paranoid.
Come on.

46:19.310 --> 46:22.145
Carson, my mom's
gonna see you. Come on.

46:24.916 --> 46:27.917
[birds cawing]

46:34.025 --> 46:35.424
- How'd it go out there today?

46:35.527 --> 46:39.328
- Eh, got a look at it
a few times,

46:39.430 --> 46:41.030
but she's got a tracker on.

46:41.099 --> 46:43.699
- Oh, really?
- Yep.

46:43.802 --> 46:45.601
Can't kill them
if they are tagged

46:45.703 --> 46:47.770
unless you find out why first.

46:49.474 --> 46:51.607
She's safe for now

46:51.709 --> 46:54.243
until I can get the contact
info off the tracker.

46:54.345 --> 46:56.946
- Well, that's too bad.

46:57.048 --> 46:58.114
- Mm.

46:58.216 --> 46:59.782
- Hmm.

47:12.197 --> 47:13.830
Oh, hey, Carson.

47:15.900 --> 47:17.700
- You know, you might have
everyone else fooled,

47:17.802 --> 47:19.335
but not me.

47:19.437 --> 47:20.870
Nothing is happening
with you and Ali

47:20.972 --> 47:22.138
as long as
I'm in the picture, okay?

47:22.240 --> 47:24.340
- Dude, what are you
even talking about?

47:24.442 --> 47:25.875
- I don't care
what you tell Diana.

47:25.977 --> 47:27.643
I want you out
of that house and gone

47:27.745 --> 47:29.645
by the time we get back
from Ali's art thing

47:29.747 --> 47:34.150
or I'm gonna show
everyone this, Daniel.

47:34.252 --> 47:37.086
- You took a picture
of my ID, Carson?

47:37.188 --> 47:38.454
- Doesn't look like
it's your ID.

47:38.556 --> 47:39.856
- It may not look
like it's my ID,

47:39.958 --> 47:41.290
but it's just
a bad picture, okay?

47:41.392 --> 47:42.892
It's mine.

47:42.994 --> 47:44.527
- You know, you're right.
I wasn't sure either,

47:44.629 --> 47:48.264
so I just checked
my mom's employee records.

47:48.366 --> 47:49.665
You know, maybe you're
Daniel Kennedy,

47:49.767 --> 47:52.468
but maybe you're not,

47:52.570 --> 47:54.904
but nothing else
you've told anyone is true.

47:55.006 --> 47:57.807
<i> [tense music]</i>

47:57.909 --> 48:03.446
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

48:03.548 --> 48:06.415
Gone. Tonight.

49:22.327 --> 49:25.161
<i> [ominous music]</i>

49:25.263 --> 49:29.065
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

49:29.167 --> 49:32.001
[chain rattles]

49:32.103 --> 49:36.505
Oh, oh, no, no, no, what the
hell are you doing here, man?

49:36.607 --> 49:40.042
- I just can't have you getting
in the way anymore, Carson.

49:40.144 --> 49:42.678
She belongs to me.

49:42.780 --> 49:44.313
- What are you saying?

49:47.618 --> 49:49.051
Um...

49:52.390 --> 49:54.357
Okay, dude,
what a--what are you doing?

49:54.459 --> 49:56.659
Dude, are you insane?
What--what the hell?

49:56.761 --> 50:01.998
- They say love makes you
do crazy things.

50:02.100 --> 50:06.535
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

50:08.439 --> 50:10.106
- Ow. Ah, ah.

50:10.208 --> 50:13.509
Ah, ah, ow.

50:15.813 --> 50:17.580
- How you, uh,
hanging in there?

50:17.682 --> 50:19.048
- Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

50:19.150 --> 50:20.816
Daniel,
what are you doing?

50:20.918 --> 50:23.853
Ah, oh, my God.

50:23.955 --> 50:27.156
Ow, ow, ah, ah,
what are you doing?

50:27.258 --> 50:29.558
- Unlock.
- No, no, dude, dude,

50:29.660 --> 50:30.860
dude, dude, put me down.

50:30.962 --> 50:32.628
Daniel, this isn't funny.
Let me down.

50:32.730 --> 50:34.563
- Oh, that's exactly
what I'm gonna do.

50:39.270 --> 50:40.469
There he goes.

50:41.806 --> 50:43.839
- Daniel, what are you doing?
Jesus.

50:43.941 --> 50:45.307
Stop, dude.

50:45.410 --> 50:48.511
[yelling]

50:48.613 --> 50:50.780
Help me!
Somebody help me!

50:50.882 --> 50:52.248
[device beeping]

50:52.350 --> 50:55.384
- Ah, the tracker says
it's feeding time.

50:57.388 --> 51:00.222
[hydraulics whirring]

51:00.324 --> 51:01.824
- [yelling]

51:01.926 --> 51:03.759
Dude, stop!
Daniel, Daniel, please!

51:03.861 --> 51:07.897
I'm s--oh, my God.
Daniel, Daniel, Daniel!

51:13.805 --> 51:16.939
Daniel, you will never get her,
okay? Please let me go.

51:18.209 --> 51:21.343
- My Ali will always
come back to me.

51:21.446 --> 51:23.446
- She doesn't want you,
man, okay?

51:23.548 --> 51:25.347
Please just let me down, man.

51:27.618 --> 51:28.951
[buzzer sounds]

51:32.256 --> 51:35.257
- [gasping]

51:55.913 --> 51:57.046
- Dan.

51:57.148 --> 51:58.481
- That looks great on you.

51:58.583 --> 52:00.416
- Thanks.
- I'm sorry.

52:00.518 --> 52:02.852
I didn't mean to scare you.

52:02.954 --> 52:04.487
- It's fine, just please
knock next time.

52:04.589 --> 52:06.622
- Here, let me help you
with that.

52:11.729 --> 52:14.697
I always love it when you wear
your hair like that.

52:14.799 --> 52:16.599
- Have you seen it
like this before?

52:16.701 --> 52:18.267
- Yeah, I think so,

52:18.369 --> 52:21.370
in one of the pictures
downstairs or something.

52:21.472 --> 52:22.938
- Probably.
[cell phone chimes]

52:23.040 --> 52:24.240
Oh.

52:27.278 --> 52:28.978
You gotta be kidding me.

52:29.080 --> 52:31.847
- Is everything okay?
- No, it's not.

52:37.722 --> 52:39.522
<i> - This is Carson,</i>
<i> and if this is Derek,</i>

52:39.624 --> 52:41.123
<i> please don't leave a message.</i>
- I don't believe this.

52:41.225 --> 52:42.424
Carson's blowing me off.

52:42.527 --> 52:44.894
- What? Why?

52:44.996 --> 52:45.861
- He says he got held up,

52:45.963 --> 52:47.129
which means his teammates

52:47.231 --> 52:49.565
probably
dragged him out somewhere.

52:49.667 --> 52:51.634
- Does he always choose
his friends over you?

52:51.736 --> 52:54.436
- No, it's not like that.

52:54.539 --> 52:56.338
His priorities
just aren't exactly

52:56.440 --> 52:57.706
how I'd like them
to be.

52:57.808 --> 52:59.942
- Ali, honestly,
you shouldn't settle

53:00.044 --> 53:02.545
for being someone's
second priority.

53:02.647 --> 53:05.114
A girl like you deserves
way more than that.

53:06.217 --> 53:08.984
- Thank you. That's very sweet.

53:09.086 --> 53:10.486
You mind unzipping me now?

53:10.588 --> 53:12.788
- Why?

53:12.890 --> 53:15.224
- No date. No ride.
We're already late.

53:15.326 --> 53:16.825
Honestly, I'm not really
in the mood anymore.

53:16.928 --> 53:20.229
- That's a shame.
You worked so hard for this.

53:20.331 --> 53:21.864
You have to go
enjoy it, Ali.

53:21.966 --> 53:24.800
Honestly, you're gonna let him
ruin that for you?

53:26.537 --> 53:28.971
- Do you have plans tonight?
- Yeah, as a matter of fact,

53:29.073 --> 53:31.373
I was thinking I might
just go to an art show.

53:38.849 --> 53:40.349
I can't believe you took these.

53:40.451 --> 53:41.617
- You like them?
- Yeah, they're amazing.

53:41.719 --> 53:43.285
You're a true talent.

53:43.387 --> 53:46.021
I always knew you'd do
something special, Alison.

53:46.123 --> 53:48.257
- Alison, dear.
- Hi, Suze.

53:48.359 --> 53:49.792
- Congratulations.

53:49.894 --> 53:51.493
- Thank you so much
for hosting this event.

53:51.596 --> 53:53.362
It's such an honor
to have my work displayed here.

53:53.464 --> 53:57.399
- Of course. Where's Carson?
Wasn't he coming tonight?

53:57.501 --> 53:59.935
- Carson couldn't make it.
- Really?

54:00.037 --> 54:02.238
I trust there's
no trouble in paradise?

54:02.340 --> 54:04.640
- No, he just
had other plans.

54:04.742 --> 54:06.642
- Well, I wouldn't take it
too personally.

54:06.744 --> 54:09.678
- You know, I was accepted
into Albertus for the fall.

54:09.780 --> 54:11.347
I was hoping to get into
their photography program.

54:11.449 --> 54:13.415
- Yes, Carson
mentioned that.

54:13.517 --> 54:14.750
You know,
my old roommate Janet

54:14.852 --> 54:16.518
runs that department,
I believe.

54:16.621 --> 54:19.288
It's very competitive.
Congratulations.

54:19.390 --> 54:21.724
- Oh, I know.
Actually, I was hoping

54:21.826 --> 54:23.659
maybe if you didn't mind
if you could put--

54:23.761 --> 54:25.961
- Oh, Ali, let me just
stop you right there.

54:26.063 --> 54:27.396
I really don't think
it would be appropriate

54:27.498 --> 54:29.665
if I got involved.

54:29.767 --> 54:30.766
I'm sure you understand.

54:30.868 --> 54:32.401
- Yeah, I understand.

54:32.503 --> 54:35.504
- You know, that really
is a nice picture.

54:35.606 --> 54:37.072
It's great
that you could capture

54:37.174 --> 54:40.075
one of those rare moments.

54:40.177 --> 54:41.310
Are you okay, hon?

54:41.412 --> 54:43.345
- Excuse me.

54:50.154 --> 54:53.022
- Ali, don't let her
ruin your night.

54:53.124 --> 54:55.257
You don't need her
to get into that department.

54:55.359 --> 54:58.193
- It's not that.
- Well, then what is it?

55:00.131 --> 55:02.064
- It's that picture.

55:02.166 --> 55:03.365
That's not who
my parents were.

55:03.467 --> 55:05.834
They were just
constantly fighting.

55:05.936 --> 55:07.269
- That's what happens

55:07.371 --> 55:09.438
when people
love each other, you know?

55:09.540 --> 55:12.374
You have disagreements,
but you forgive each other.

55:12.476 --> 55:14.610
- They hadn't been
happy for years.

55:14.712 --> 55:18.614
The only reason they were still
together was because of Kevin.

55:18.716 --> 55:22.184
Even the night my dad died,
they'd been going at it.

55:22.286 --> 55:25.187
Everything outside of the house
was just for show.

55:25.289 --> 55:27.856
I'm not crazy about Ted,
but at least he makes

55:27.958 --> 55:32.127
my mom happy, happier
than I've ever seen her.

55:32.229 --> 55:36.198
- You don't have to make
the same mistakes they did.

55:36.300 --> 55:39.935
- Carson wants to move
in together after graduation.

55:40.037 --> 55:44.473
I do love him,
but we're still so young.

55:44.575 --> 55:48.310
What if that all changes
tomorrow or ten years from now?

55:48.412 --> 55:49.778
How do you know?

55:49.880 --> 55:51.847
- You just know
when it's right.

55:53.484 --> 55:56.652
Maybe you guys aren't
meant to be together.

55:58.122 --> 55:59.722
- Maybe.

56:02.093 --> 56:03.425
Okay, what was that?

56:03.527 --> 56:06.362
- I'm--I'm so sorry.
That was wrong.

56:06.464 --> 56:08.163
I meant to be a friend
right now.

56:08.265 --> 56:10.933
I--nothing--nothing more.

56:15.373 --> 56:17.906
- Please don't tell Carson.

56:19.610 --> 56:21.410
We should probably go back.

56:23.447 --> 56:24.947
- You know what?

56:27.218 --> 56:29.284
I'm not sorry I did it.

56:43.401 --> 56:46.268
Good morning.
I hope you are hungry.

56:46.370 --> 56:49.671
- What's all this?
- Oh, this is a celebration.

56:49.774 --> 56:51.607
- What are we celebrating?
- You and me.

56:51.709 --> 56:53.275
- Oh.

56:54.812 --> 56:56.245
Ali, I know things
have been hard in the past,

56:56.347 --> 56:57.713
but everything's gonna
work out this time.

56:57.815 --> 56:59.581
- Daniel, what are
you talking about?

56:59.683 --> 57:02.918
- Our future, everything that
we've dreamed of together.

57:03.020 --> 57:05.053
- Okay, slow down.
I'm sorry if I gave you

57:05.156 --> 57:07.823
the wrong impression
last night, but...

57:07.925 --> 57:09.558
- What?

57:09.660 --> 57:12.261
- I have a boyfriend, Daniel.
You know that.

57:12.363 --> 57:14.763
- I took care of that.
- What does that mean?

57:14.865 --> 57:16.632
- We're gonna be
together finally.

57:16.734 --> 57:19.568
- It was just a kiss.
It doesn't mean anything.

57:29.847 --> 57:32.314
- You can't do this
to me again, Alison!

57:32.416 --> 57:33.949
I'm who you're
supposed to be with!

57:34.051 --> 57:36.084
It's our destiny, okay?

57:36.187 --> 57:38.687
Bruce and Ali,
that is how the story goes.

57:38.789 --> 57:40.456
- Who's Bruce?

57:40.558 --> 57:42.891
- Oh, don't be afraid of me,
Ali. You're my everything.

57:42.993 --> 57:44.293
I can't be without you.
- Don't touch me.

57:44.395 --> 57:46.895
- You are my world, okay?
I can't--

57:46.997 --> 57:48.397
- Get out of my house!

57:48.499 --> 57:49.531
- You, me, and Kevin,
we'll be a family.

57:49.633 --> 57:50.799
- I said get the hell out!
Stop!

57:50.901 --> 57:52.301
- Get your hands off of her!

57:52.403 --> 57:55.370
- Di, no, you don't understand.
- No, no, no,

57:55.473 --> 57:57.940
you don't understand.
You put your hands on her,

57:58.042 --> 58:01.310
I put my hands on you,
understood?

58:01.412 --> 58:03.679
Now, you heard her.
Get the hell out of the house.

58:06.917 --> 58:11.186
- Okay, if that's
what you want.

58:20.231 --> 58:21.630
- Mom, he's a psycho.

58:21.732 --> 58:23.065
- We'll change the locks
this afternoon.

58:23.167 --> 58:24.399
- Okay, yeah.

58:28.172 --> 58:31.039
<i> [tense music]</i>

58:31.141 --> 58:36.612
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

58:36.714 --> 58:38.947
[car engine revs]

58:39.049 --> 58:42.084
- [screaming]

58:49.460 --> 58:51.193
- So, wait,
she kicked him out?

58:51.295 --> 58:53.061
- Yeah, it was
kind of impressive.

58:53.163 --> 58:54.897
- Did he hit on you
or something?

58:54.999 --> 58:56.665
- Something like that.

58:56.767 --> 58:59.401
- Now I know
why he didn't call me back.

58:59.503 --> 59:03.071
Speaking of which,
still nothing from Carson?

59:03.173 --> 59:05.941
- He wasn't in school today.
I'm getting really worried.

59:06.043 --> 59:07.876
- Yeah, I am too,

59:07.978 --> 59:10.946
worried that you keep putting
up with his constant ghosting.

59:11.048 --> 59:12.881
- He doesn't ghost me.

59:12.983 --> 59:14.349
This isn't someone
from your endless stream

59:14.451 --> 59:16.952
of faceless
one night stands, Rhi.

59:17.054 --> 59:20.188
- Excuse you?

59:20.291 --> 59:21.790
- I didn't mean it
like that.

59:21.892 --> 59:23.258
- No, I--I think you did.

59:23.360 --> 59:25.027
- I just meant
Carson's different.

59:25.129 --> 59:26.361
We have history.

59:26.463 --> 59:29.431
- You know, some of us
don't want to settle

59:29.533 --> 59:32.301
for just being
comfortable and safe.

59:33.637 --> 59:35.571
- Rhi?

59:35.673 --> 59:37.539
Don't you want
a ride home?

59:37.641 --> 59:40.208
- I'd rather walk,
thanks.

59:42.713 --> 59:45.547
<i> [ominous music]</i>

59:45.649 --> 59:47.649
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

59:47.751 --> 59:49.885
- "You can't let me go again
that easily,

59:49.987 --> 59:55.023
Bruce, not after we found
each other again."

59:55.125 --> 59:58.660
"I promise, Alison,
I won't let you go.

59:58.762 --> 1:00:00.929
You're my everything."

1:00:03.267 --> 1:00:04.800
[cell phone chimes]

1:00:09.740 --> 1:00:11.974
[chuckles]

1:00:12.076 --> 1:00:13.742
[doorbell rings]

1:00:15.279 --> 1:00:17.112
- I was, uh,
beginning to think

1:00:17.214 --> 1:00:18.914
you didn't want
to see me again.

1:00:19.016 --> 1:00:22.951
- Not at all, especially when
you wear my favorite dress.

1:00:23.053 --> 1:00:26.221
- You're weird,
but that's okay.

1:00:26.323 --> 1:00:28.056
So am I.

1:00:29.560 --> 1:00:30.993
Nice place.

1:00:32.329 --> 1:00:35.163
- So have you spoken
to Ali at all?

1:00:35.265 --> 1:00:37.566
- This morning.

1:00:37.668 --> 1:00:39.635
- Did she say anything
about me?

1:00:39.737 --> 1:00:41.837
- Everything.

1:00:41.939 --> 1:00:44.139
She told me
I shouldn't see you.

1:00:45.609 --> 1:00:47.476
- Well, then what
are you doing here?

1:00:47.578 --> 1:00:49.444
- I don't like being told
what to do.

1:00:49.546 --> 1:00:51.179
- Is that so?
- Mm-hmm.

1:00:51.281 --> 1:00:52.481
You, sir,
might have even caused

1:00:52.583 --> 1:00:54.116
a little fight
between us.

1:00:54.218 --> 1:00:56.385
- Well, I hope
it was nothing serious.

1:00:56.487 --> 1:01:00.122
- I'll be the bigger person,
reach out when she cools down.

1:01:00.224 --> 1:01:03.692
- Well, I wish you guys
all the best then.

1:01:03.794 --> 1:01:06.428
- So want to give me a tour?

1:01:06.530 --> 1:01:09.097
- This is pretty--
pretty much it.

1:01:11.001 --> 1:01:13.935
- Is that, uh, where you
keep the dead bodies?

1:01:15.472 --> 1:01:18.507
- As a matter of fact,
yes, it is.

1:01:18.609 --> 1:01:20.075
[both chuckle]

1:01:22.579 --> 1:01:24.446
Do you want to see
the bedroom?

1:01:25.516 --> 1:01:28.216
- Okay.
- Okay.

1:01:33.057 --> 1:01:35.490
<i> - This is Carson,</i>
<i> and if this is Derek,</i>

1:01:35.592 --> 1:01:36.758
<i> please don't leave a message.</i>

1:01:36.860 --> 1:01:38.226
- Carson, I don't know
what's going on,

1:01:38.328 --> 1:01:41.430
but please call me back.

1:01:52.643 --> 1:01:55.410
<i> [ominous music]</i>

1:01:55.512 --> 1:02:02.451
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:02:10.961 --> 1:02:13.962
[keys jingle]

1:02:26.043 --> 1:02:28.844
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

1:02:28.946 --> 1:02:35.851
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:03:07.551 --> 1:03:08.450
- [gasps]

1:03:08.552 --> 1:03:11.086
- I see you've met Daniel.

1:03:11.188 --> 1:03:14.422
Poor guy,
he was in the wrong place

1:03:14.525 --> 1:03:17.092
at the wrong time
with the right face.

1:03:19.596 --> 1:03:21.196
Are you looking for your mace?

1:03:23.534 --> 1:03:28.804
- Look, I'm not gonna tell
anyone, but I'm gonna go.

1:03:33.010 --> 1:03:36.678
- I didn't want to kill him,

1:03:36.780 --> 1:03:40.215
but I needed his reality.

1:03:40.317 --> 1:03:42.184
Bruce Kane was dead.

1:03:45.222 --> 1:03:46.721
What was I supposed to do?

1:03:46.824 --> 1:03:49.257
- Don't come any closer
or I'll send it.

1:03:51.862 --> 1:03:54.796
- You seem like a really
sweet girl, Rhiannon.

1:03:54.898 --> 1:03:56.364
- Let me go.

1:03:56.466 --> 1:03:58.733
- You really shouldn't have
come down here.

1:04:00.637 --> 1:04:02.938
<i> [intense music]</i>

1:04:03.040 --> 1:04:05.307
- [gasping]

1:04:13.717 --> 1:04:16.251
[gasping]

1:04:16.353 --> 1:04:23.158
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:04:24.494 --> 1:04:25.660
- Stop.

1:04:32.069 --> 1:04:34.569
- Okay, let's talk about this.

1:04:34.671 --> 1:04:38.340
- I just wanted a friend
for my wife.

1:04:38.442 --> 1:04:41.209
<i> [intense frantic music]</i>

1:04:41.311 --> 1:04:46.882
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:04:46.984 --> 1:04:49.217
[phone thuds loudly]

1:04:53.690 --> 1:04:56.491
What have you done, huh?

1:05:04.868 --> 1:05:06.568
[cell phone chimes]

1:05:12.809 --> 1:05:15.610
<i> [intense music]</i>

1:05:15.712 --> 1:05:22.617
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:05:27.691 --> 1:05:28.957
Need a ride?

1:06:11.601 --> 1:06:15.570
<i> My only regret is that I</i>
<i> couldn't get there any sooner.</i>

1:06:15.672 --> 1:06:18.840
<i> Maybe then we could be</i>
<i> celebrating two saved lives.</i>

1:06:18.942 --> 1:06:21.710
<i> - The hero of Hunter's Cove</i>
<i> who recently helped rescue</i>

1:06:21.812 --> 1:06:24.212
<i> a young girl from the jaws</i>
<i> of a bloodthirsty shark</i>

1:06:24.314 --> 1:06:26.781
<i> is going out to search</i>
<i> for the massive predator.</i>

1:06:26.883 --> 1:06:28.683
<i> Bruce Kane</i>
<i> is setting sail today,</i>

1:06:28.785 --> 1:06:30.785
<i> determined to track down</i>
<i> that very shark</i>

1:06:30.887 --> 1:06:32.420
<i> that took</i>
<i> Nicholas Jordan's life.</i>

1:06:32.522 --> 1:06:34.856
<i> - Bruce Kane, son of</i>
<i> State Rep Richard Kane,</i>

1:06:34.958 --> 1:06:37.459
<i> believed to be dead</i>
<i> after abducting Laura Wilcox,</i>

1:06:37.561 --> 1:06:39.260
<i> the same girl he saved</i>
<i> from a shark attack</i>

1:06:39.363 --> 1:06:40.695
<i> just two weeks ago.</i>

1:06:40.797 --> 1:06:42.664
<i> The Wilcoxes claim</i>
<i> that Bruce Kane</i>

1:06:42.766 --> 1:06:44.432
<i> had been stalking her when</i>
<i> things took a violent turn.</i>

1:06:44.534 --> 1:06:46.935
<i> Ms. Wilcox also claims</i>
<i> he's responsible for the death</i>

1:06:47.037 --> 1:06:50.739
<i> of her former high school</i>
<i> sweetheart Alex Vaughn.</i>

1:06:50.841 --> 1:06:52.073
- [exhales sharply]

1:06:53.477 --> 1:06:56.578
Mom? Please call me.
It's an emergency.

1:06:56.680 --> 1:06:58.913
Kevin, don't walk home
from practice,

1:06:59.016 --> 1:07:03.752
and if you see Daniel,
stay away from him, okay?

1:07:03.854 --> 1:07:06.654
<i> [intense music]</i>

1:07:06.757 --> 1:07:13.628
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:07:21.071 --> 1:07:23.838
- Kev?

1:07:23.940 --> 1:07:25.907
Kev, is that you?

1:07:31.281 --> 1:07:32.447
Kevin.

1:07:34.818 --> 1:07:37.218
- [muffled screaming]

1:07:37.320 --> 1:07:39.054
[Taser clicking]
- Beautiful Diana.

1:07:47.197 --> 1:07:48.696
- We'll be with you
in a moment. You can sit there.

1:07:48.799 --> 1:07:51.332
- Please, it's an emergency.
- Just a minute, please.

1:07:54.438 --> 1:07:56.471
[cell phone chimes]

1:08:00.310 --> 1:08:02.210
[cell phone rings]

1:08:03.713 --> 1:08:05.413
- What the hell do you
think you're doing?

1:08:05.515 --> 1:08:09.918
<i> - Kevin and I were just about</i>
<i> to do a little fishing.</i>

1:08:10.020 --> 1:08:11.920
- I know who you are, Bruce.

1:08:12.022 --> 1:08:13.655
I'm at the police station
right now.

1:08:13.757 --> 1:08:18.860
<i> - Oh, don't be stupid, Alison.</i>

1:08:18.962 --> 1:08:20.495
- What do you want?

1:08:20.597 --> 1:08:23.131
<i> - I want this story</i>
<i> to have a happy ending.</i>

1:08:23.233 --> 1:08:26.301
<i> You stay on the phone, okay?</i>
<i> Leave the station now,</i>

1:08:26.403 --> 1:08:30.071
<i> don't tell anyone anything,</i>
<i> and head to the club.</i>

1:08:30.173 --> 1:08:32.674
- Okay, Miss,
what did you want?

1:08:35.479 --> 1:08:38.913
<i> - Leave now.</i>

1:09:05.542 --> 1:09:08.209
You can hang up now.

1:09:08.311 --> 1:09:09.878
- Daniel.
I mean--

1:09:09.980 --> 1:09:11.913
- We don't have
to pretend anymore.

1:09:12.015 --> 1:09:14.349
You can call me Bruce.

1:09:14.451 --> 1:09:16.151
Have a seat.

1:09:16.253 --> 1:09:18.219
- Where's Kevin?
- Oh, he's fine, Ali.

1:09:18.321 --> 1:09:20.488
He's fine.
Have a seat.

1:09:20.590 --> 1:09:22.190
Sit!

1:09:38.175 --> 1:09:41.609
- What are you doing?

1:09:41.711 --> 1:09:43.611
- I don't want to hurt you.

1:09:43.713 --> 1:09:45.013
I don't want to hurt
any of you.

1:09:45.115 --> 1:09:49.284
I just--Ali,
I want to be with you.

1:09:50.320 --> 1:09:52.187
You came back to me.

1:09:52.289 --> 1:09:53.922
It gives me purpose, okay?

1:09:54.024 --> 1:09:56.090
I'm not gonna take that
for granted.

1:09:56.193 --> 1:09:59.794
- Whatever you want,
just leave Kevin out of this.

1:09:59.896 --> 1:10:01.729
- Ali, we're gonna be a family.

1:10:01.831 --> 1:10:03.898
- What?
- I don't have a lot of time

1:10:04.000 --> 1:10:10.004
before they find out
about Ted and Rhi and Carson.

1:10:10.106 --> 1:10:13.575
- What did you do to them?
- Baby, don't be upset.

1:10:13.677 --> 1:10:15.410
You know, we have
some mending to do,

1:10:15.512 --> 1:10:17.145
but we gotta get out of here.
We really do need to go, okay?

1:10:17.247 --> 1:10:18.413
- What?

1:10:18.515 --> 1:10:21.015
- You're gonna come with me,
Alison!

1:10:21.117 --> 1:10:23.318
I'm sorry.
That was uncalled for.

1:10:23.420 --> 1:10:25.587
Um, have some wine.

1:10:25.689 --> 1:10:29.057
This is--this is a lot
to absorb, and I am sorry.

1:10:31.795 --> 1:10:34.395
"Well, I--I
forgive you, Bruce."

1:10:36.833 --> 1:10:38.399
- I forgive you, Bruce.

1:10:40.337 --> 1:10:43.438
- We love each other,
and that's all that matters.

1:10:43.540 --> 1:10:46.007
Everything's just gonna
sort itself out, right?

1:10:46.910 --> 1:10:48.676
- Yes.

1:10:50.146 --> 1:10:51.679
- Whew.

1:10:51.781 --> 1:10:53.948
Well...

1:10:57.654 --> 1:10:59.854
Allison...

1:11:02.158 --> 1:11:03.691
Will you marry me?

1:11:10.567 --> 1:11:12.700
I want to hear you say it.

1:11:14.704 --> 1:11:16.504
- Yes. Yes, Bruce.

1:11:16.606 --> 1:11:20.408
[both breathing heavily]

1:11:21.711 --> 1:11:23.811
- Aren't you gonna
give your fiancé a kiss?

1:11:29.219 --> 1:11:30.785
Well, now that that's
all out of the way,

1:11:30.887 --> 1:11:32.720
let's just enjoy ourselves
a nice dinner, right?

1:11:32.822 --> 1:11:36.090
We, uh, have all the time in
the world to work things out.

1:11:36.192 --> 1:11:37.425
Kevin?

1:11:37.527 --> 1:11:40.528
[tray rattling]

1:11:41.431 --> 1:11:42.964
- Kevin.

1:11:47.437 --> 1:11:49.771
- Ali,

1:11:49.873 --> 1:11:51.572
tell your brother
the wonderful news.

1:11:52.575 --> 1:11:55.643
- Bruce and I are engaged.

1:11:55.745 --> 1:11:58.479
- Isn't that wonderful, Kev?

1:11:58.581 --> 1:12:00.782
Your beautiful sister
is gonna walk down the aisle

1:12:00.884 --> 1:12:02.483
with the man of her dreams.

1:12:04.321 --> 1:12:05.486
- Run, Kevin! Run!

1:12:05.588 --> 1:12:08.589
- [screaming]

1:12:11.661 --> 1:12:13.594
- Wait! We need to get Mom!

1:12:13.697 --> 1:12:15.063
- Where's Mom?
- I don't know!

1:12:15.165 --> 1:12:18.032
[electricity zapping]
[screams]

1:12:18.134 --> 1:12:20.935
[Taser clicking]
- Oh, oh!

1:12:21.037 --> 1:12:24.105
- I am very disappointed
in you, Alison.

1:12:38.088 --> 1:12:39.821
- [muffled]
Ali!

1:12:43.626 --> 1:12:45.326
Ali!

1:12:48.365 --> 1:12:50.031
[tools clang]

1:12:50.133 --> 1:12:51.766
Ali!

1:12:54.704 --> 1:12:56.738
- Mom!
- Ali.

1:12:58.742 --> 1:13:00.074
- Where is he?
- I didn't see where he went.

1:13:00.176 --> 1:13:01.409
- Where's Kevin?
- I didn't see him,

1:13:01.511 --> 1:13:03.644
but you run. Go get help.

1:13:03.747 --> 1:13:05.480
- No, I'm getting you
out of there.

1:13:05.582 --> 1:13:07.281
- Go get help!

1:13:08.718 --> 1:13:12.687
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God, Mom.
[whimpers]

1:13:12.789 --> 1:13:15.656
<i> [eerie synth music]</i>

1:13:15.759 --> 1:13:22.363
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:13:35.845 --> 1:13:38.813
[hydraulics whirring]

1:13:42.519 --> 1:13:45.219
[whimpers]
I'm coming, Mom!

1:13:52.295 --> 1:13:55.897
- I need you to come with me
out of your own free will, Ali.

1:13:55.999 --> 1:13:58.633
I need it to be real this time.

1:13:58.735 --> 1:14:01.369
- Don't do this, Bruce, please.
- I told you.

1:14:01.471 --> 1:14:03.204
I told you that
we were gonna be a family

1:14:03.306 --> 1:14:04.939
and that we were gonna be happy

1:14:05.041 --> 1:14:07.041
and that I was
gonna protect you.

1:14:07.143 --> 1:14:11.345
- Daniel?
- Stop talking, Diana, God.

1:14:16.920 --> 1:14:20.188
Now, we can really do this
with or without your mom,

1:14:20.290 --> 1:14:22.824
but that is gonna
be up to you, Ali.

1:14:41.244 --> 1:14:43.277
We are running out of time.

1:14:43.379 --> 1:14:45.813
- Please stop.
- Don't you want your mom

1:14:45.915 --> 1:14:46.981
to be at our wedding?

1:14:47.083 --> 1:14:49.183
- Bruce, please!

1:14:52.155 --> 1:14:54.222
Please stop!
Mom! Mom!

1:14:56.960 --> 1:14:58.292
- Oh.

1:15:27.190 --> 1:15:29.757
Oh.

1:15:29.859 --> 1:15:32.860
<i> [intense music]</i>

1:15:32.962 --> 1:15:34.795
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:15:34.898 --> 1:15:36.264
- [gasps]

1:15:45.141 --> 1:15:46.340
Are you ready to start talking?

1:15:46.442 --> 1:15:48.342
- Leave my daughter
out of this!

1:15:48.444 --> 1:15:50.177
- Shut up, Diana.

1:15:55.852 --> 1:15:57.418
- I'll go with you, Bruce.

1:15:57.520 --> 1:15:59.153
- You know,
I don't believe you.

1:15:59.255 --> 1:16:01.088
- I'll do whatever you want!
What do you want me to do?

1:16:01.190 --> 1:16:02.857
- I want you to love me.
- I do love you!

1:16:02.959 --> 1:16:04.492
- I don't believe you.

1:16:04.594 --> 1:16:06.460
- Please, Bruce! Bruce.

1:16:06.563 --> 1:16:08.729
- If you mean it,
then tell me why.

1:16:08.831 --> 1:16:11.632
- I love you because--because
you protect me

1:16:11.734 --> 1:16:17.004
and--and because you saved
Kevin and me, and--and--

1:16:17.106 --> 1:16:19.640
- And?
- You--Bruce and Ali

1:16:19.742 --> 1:16:23.978
are meant to be together.
That's how the story ends.

1:16:24.080 --> 1:16:27.982
I'll do whatever you want,
just let my mom out, please.

1:16:32.555 --> 1:16:35.323
- Open the cage.

1:16:35.425 --> 1:16:37.391
Careful, that's--that's
the only copy.

1:16:39.362 --> 1:16:42.630
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

1:16:42.732 --> 1:16:49.570
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:17:02.218 --> 1:17:03.384
Get in.

1:17:03.486 --> 1:17:06.287
- Oh, my God, what?

1:17:06.389 --> 1:17:08.422
- Di, out.

1:17:08.524 --> 1:17:10.358
- I am not letting her in here.

1:17:10.460 --> 1:17:12.927
- Out!

1:17:13.029 --> 1:17:15.896
I'm sorry to do this to you,
but I can't afford to lose you.

1:17:15.999 --> 1:17:18.165
- I know--I know what you did
to that girl,

1:17:18.267 --> 1:17:20.601
the other girl with the shark.

1:17:20.703 --> 1:17:22.737
- You mean this shark?

1:17:22.839 --> 1:17:24.038
'Cause I tracked her here.

1:17:24.140 --> 1:17:26.273
I fed her
so she wouldn't leave.

1:17:26.376 --> 1:17:29.810
She spared my life,
gave me purpose.

1:17:31.714 --> 1:17:33.047
[screams]

1:17:33.149 --> 1:17:34.548
[buzzer sounds]

1:17:34.651 --> 1:17:37.451
<i> [intense music]</i>

1:17:37.553 --> 1:17:44.392
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:17:57.840 --> 1:17:58.906
- [gags]

1:18:16.492 --> 1:18:18.225
- Get your hands off my son!

1:18:18.327 --> 1:18:20.294
- How good's that aim, Di?

1:18:20.396 --> 1:18:21.595
[screams]

1:18:21.698 --> 1:18:23.230
- Shoot him, Mom!
[gunshot]

1:18:26.369 --> 1:18:29.203
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

1:18:29.305 --> 1:18:36.110
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:19:02.238 --> 1:19:05.239
- [gasping]

1:19:08.244 --> 1:19:11.078
<i> [tender piano music]</i>

1:19:11.180 --> 1:19:18.119
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

1:19:19.088 --> 1:19:21.355
- Oh, my God.

1:19:24.260 --> 1:19:27.461
I'm so glad you're safe.
I'm so proud of you.

1:19:27.563 --> 1:19:29.663
I love you guys.

1:19:32.301 --> 1:19:33.934
<i> - Is he gone?</i>

1:19:34.036 --> 1:19:36.504
<i> - Yeah, looks like that shark</i>
<i> finally got him.</i>

1:19:42.311 --> 1:19:44.345
- [grunts]

1:19:45.448 --> 1:19:46.747
Can we go home?

1:19:46.849 --> 1:19:49.083
- Please.
